titles: The debate betweene Pride and Lowlines, pleaded to an issue in assise and hovve a iurie vvith great indifferencie being impannelled, and redy to haue geuen their verdict, were straungely intercepted, no lesse pleasant then profitable. F.T. Seene, and allowed.
author: F. T., fl. 1577.
publisher: By Iohn Charlwood, for Rafe Newbery, dwelling in Fleetestrete a litle aboue the Condite,
notes: Reproduction of a photostat of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
